            "id": "id-754c31c0-0f27-41bc-9636-c16886821d89",
            "input": "${formatting({ align: 'left', indent: '2em' })}\n$\n\\def\\D{\\Delta}\n\\def\\iddots{{\\kern3mu\\raise1mu{.}\\kern3mu\\raise6mu{.}\\kern3mu\\raise12mu{.}}}\n$\nGiven a function $f:\\mathbb R \\rightarrow \\mathbb R$ and $n$ observations $f(0), f(1), ..., f(n-1)$, then for $i,j \\in \\mathbb Z$, $0 \\le i,j \\le n-1$, define the forward differences $\\D^i_j$ as follows:\n$$\n\\begin{array}{ccccccccc}\nf(0) &        & f(1)    &        & f(2)       &            & f(3)       & \\dots   & f(n-2)     &            & f(n-1) \\\\\n     & \\D^1_0 &         & \\D^1_1 &            & \\D^1_2     &            & \\dots   &            & \\D^1_{n-2} &        \\\\\n     &        & \\D^2_0  &        & \\D^2_1     &            & \\D^2_2     & \\dots   & \\D^2_{n-3} &            &        \\\\\n     &        &         & \\ddots &            & \\ddots     &            & \\iddots &            &            &        \\\\\n     &        &         &        & \\D^{n-2}_0 &            & \\D^{n-2}_1 &         &            &            &        \\\\\n     &        &         &        &            & \\D^{n-1}_0 &            &         &            &            &        \\\\\n\\end{array}\n$$\nwhere each $\\D^i_j$ if the result of subtracting its left parent from its right parent.\n\nWith $\\D^0_j = f(j)$, each $\\D^i_j$ can be computed directly from the observed values:\n$$\n\\begin{align}\n\\D^i_j &= \\sum_{k=0}^{i}{(-1)^k{i \\choose k}f(j+k)} \\\\\n\\end{align}\n$$\nFinally, with $C_i = \\Delta^i_0$ and $i \\in \\mathbb Z$, $0 \\le i \\le n-1$, $f$ may be approximated by $f_{(i)}$\n$$\n\\begin{align}\nf_{(i)}(x) &= \\sum_{k=0}^i C_k {x \\choose i}\n\\end{align}\n$$\nNote that:\n$$\n\\begin{align}\n{x \\choose n} = \\frac{x!}{n!(x-n)!} = \\frac{x^{\\underline{n}}}{n!} = \\frac{1}{n!}\\prod_{i=0}^{n-1}{(x-i)}\n\\end{align}\n$$",
